workflow.name: Automate lead qualification & customer support with GPT-4o-mini agents
workflow.description:
### Beginner AI Agent Duo: Lead‚ÄëQualifier Task Automator & Ecommerce Chatbot

**Status:** Ready for Use‚ÄØ‚úÖ  
**Note:** This template is built entirely with **official n8n nodes**‚Äîno community‚Äënode installation required.

---

### üìù¬†Description
This template demonstrates two beginner‚Äëfriendly AI‚Äëagent patterns that cover the most common use cases:

| Agent | Purpose | Flow Highlights |
|-------|---------|-----------------|
| **Lead‚ÄëQualifier Task Automator** | Classifies phone‚Äëcall transcripts to decide if the caller is a good bulk‚Äëorder lead. | Manual Trigger ‚Üí Code (sample data) ‚Üí AI¬†Agent (GPT‚Äë4o‚Äëmini) ‚Üí Structured¬†Output¬†Parser ‚Üí Set (clean fields) |
| **Ecommerce Chatbot** | Answers customer questions about products, bulk pricing, shipping, and returns. | Chat¬†Trigger (webhook) ‚Üí AI¬†Agent (GPT‚Äë4o‚Äëmini) with Memory ‚Üí If¬†node ‚Üí Order‚Äëplaced reply or no‚Äëop |

Both agents run on **GPT‚Äë4o‚Äëmini** and use n8n‚Äôs LangChain‚Äëpowered nodes for quick, low‚Äëcode configuration.

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è¬†How¬†to¬†Install¬†&¬†Run

1. **Import the Workflow**  
   - In n8n, go to **Workflows ‚Üí Import from File** or **Paste JSON**, then save.

2. **Add Your OpenAI¬†API Key**  
   - Go to **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí OpenAI API**.  
   - Paste your key from <https://platform.openai.com>.  
   - Select this credential in both **OpenAI Chat Model** nodes.

3. **(Optional) Select a Different Model**  
   - Default model is **gpt‚Äë4o‚Äëmini**.  
   - Change to GPT‚Äë4o, GPT‚Äë3.5‚Äëturbo, or any available model in each OpenAI node.

4. **Test the Lead‚ÄëQualifier Agent**  
   - Click **Activate**.  
   - Press **Test¬†workflow**.  
   - The Code node feeds four sample transcripts; the AI Agent returns JSON like:  
     ```json
     {
       "Name": "Jordan Lee",
       "Is Good Lead": "Yes",
       "Reasoning": "Customer requests 300 custom mugs, indicating a bulk order."
     }
     ```

5. **Test the Ecommerce Chatbot**  
   - Copy the **Webhook URL** from the **When chat message received** trigger.  
   - POST a payload like:  
     ```json
     { "message": "Hi, do you offer discounts if I buy 120 notebooks?" }
     ```  
   - The AI Agent replies with bulk‚Äëpricing info.  
   - If the customer confirms an order, it appends `*****`; the If¬†node then sends ‚ÄúYour order has been placed‚Äù.

---

### üß©¬†Customization Ideas
- **Refine Qualification Logic**‚ÄÉEdit the Task Agent‚Äôs system prompt to match your own lead criteria.  
- **Save Leads Automatically**‚ÄÉAdd Google Sheets, Airtable, or a database node after the Set node.  
- **Expand the Chatbot**‚ÄÉConnect inventory APIs, payment gateways, or CRM integrations.  
- **Adjust Memory Length**‚ÄÉChange the *Simple Memory* node‚Äôs window to retain more conversation context.

---

options.systemMessage:
You are a lead qualification assistant for an ecommerce store. Your job is to determine if a customer from a phone call is a good lead for a **bulk order**.

If they mention:
- large quantities
- logos
- team gifts
- events
- wholesale
- or any indication of buying in bulk

Then classify them as a **good lead**. Otherwise, mark them as not a good lead.

Respond only in valid JSON with:
- "Name": customer‚Äôs name
- "Is Good Lead": Yes or No
- "Reasoning": short one-sentence reason

üëã Hi there! I'm your personal assistant here to help you with anything related to our ecommerce store.

I can assist you with:
- Product information
- Bulk orders
- Pricing questions
- Customization options (like adding a logo)
- Shipping times and return policies

Here‚Äôs how I work:
- I know the details of our products, pricing, and bulk order discounts.
- I respond politely, professionally, and clearly.
- If you're placing a bulk order, I‚Äôll ask for the quantity you need, when you need it, and whether you have your artwork or logo ready.

## Product Pricing (Standard Retail):
- **Custom Notebook**: $12.00 each  
- **Eco Water Bottle**: $15.00 each  
- **Enamel Mug**: $10.00 each  
- **Canvas Tote Bag**: $14.00 each

## Bulk Discount Tiers:
- 50+ units: 10% off  
- 100+ units: 15% off  
- 250+ units: 20% off  
- 500+ units: 25% off  
*Discounts apply per product type and are automatically calculated.*

## Shipping & Returns:
- Standard shipping: 3‚Äì5 business days  
- Bulk orders may take 7‚Äì14 business days depending on customization
- Returns accepted within 30 days for non-customized items

## Rules:
- Be honest and helpful
- Never make up data or offer discounts outside the tiers above
- If unsure about something, say a team member will follow up
- If the customer mentions a bulk order, ask how many units they need and if they have artwork ready


- if the customer has confirmed they want to place an order output ***** along with the response. 

Just ask your question, and I‚Äôll take it from there!

### Need help?  
Email **rbreen@ynteractive.com**

---

### How to Install & Run

1. **Import the workflow**  
   - n8n ‚Üí **Workflows ‚Üí Import from File** (or **Paste JSON**) ‚Üí **Save**

2. **Add your OpenAI API key**  
   - n8n ‚Üí **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí OpenAI API**  
   - Paste the key from <https://platform.openai.com>  
   - Select this credential in both **OpenAI Chat Model** nodes

3. **(Optional) Choose another model**  
   - Default model: **gpt‚Äë4o‚Äëmini**  
   - Open each **OpenAI Chat Model** node ‚Üí choose **GPT‚Äë4o**, **GPT‚Äë3.5‚Äëturbo**, etc.

4. **Test the Lead‚ÄëQualifier Task Automator**  
   - Click **Activate**  
   - Press **Test workflow**  
   - Sample transcripts run; each item returns JSON with **Name**, **Is‚ÄØGood‚ÄØLead**, **Reasoning**

5. **Test the Ecommerce Chatbot**  
   - Copy the **Webhook URL** from **When chat message received**  
   - POST example payload:  
     ```json
     { "message": "Hi, do you offer discounts if I buy 120 notebooks?" }
     ```  
   - Chatbot replies with pricing details  
   - If the response contains `*****`, the **If** node sends: **‚ÄúYour order has been placed‚Äù**

---

### Customization Ideas

- Edit prompts to change lead‚Äëqualification rules or chatbot dialogue  
- Add Google Sheets, Airtable, or database nodes to store qualified leads  
- Integrate inventory, shipping, or payment APIs  
- Adjust the **Simple Memory** node‚Äôs window size to remember more conversation context

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
